    "updated_at": "2025-11-16T21:31:44Z",
    "body": "Maintenance is happening on a voluntary basis, and someone may or may not start working on this at any time.\n\nThat said, I am not surprised the presence of `\\b` is causing issues with width-calculations. If bash doesn't have the issue it is unlikely to be related to the way starship prints strings.",
