    "created_at": "2025-11-16T22:38:29Z",
    "updated_at": "2025-11-16T22:38:29Z",
    "body": "Thanks for the reply. I just wanted some sort of feedback, since I opened this issue several months ago. \nI am not pushing anyone nor asking to fix this right now. I know how projects operate and that most of the time it's unpaid and in someone's spare time.\n\nI just wanted to get an idea of what a starship dev makes of this. I am also more than happy to subscribe to the zsh mailing list and post it there. I just don't know whether this is a starship issue or a bug in zsh. Or it could be a combination of both.\n\nMaybe I am the only one in the world who uses `\\b` in the prompt. Otherwise somebody else must have noticed this behavior with zsh as well.\nI'd be stoked not to use `\\b`, if there was another way to get the same prompt. But afaik it is not possible. I tried so many different things. You can see in my 2nd video what happens if I don't use `\\b`.",
